Nelspruit Flying Squad arrested two suspects, aged 32 and 39, along the R40 between White River and Mbombela on Thursday June 9, on charges of possession of dagga. ALSO READ: House fire on R40 claims grandfather’s life A provincial police spokesperson, Brig Selvy Mohlala, said the officers were conducting their routine patrolling duties when they spotted a suspicious-looking BMW. They stopped it and upon searching, found large bags of dagga of an estimated street value of R250 000. They arrested the two suspects. ALSO READ: Three suspects to appear in Nelspruit Magistrate’s Court for possession of unlicensed firearms They are expected to appear in the White River Magistrate’s Court today, on Friday June 10. The provincial police commissioner, Lt Gen Semakaleng Manamela, applauded the members for their vigilance and alertness. This is a developing story. Lowvelder will keep its readers updated.  Do you have more information about the story? Please send us an email to editorial@lowvelder.co.za. For free breaking and community news, visit Lowvelder’s website: Lowvelder For more news and interesting articles, like Lowvelder on Facebook, follow us on Twitter or Instagram